# Cursor Platform Identity: UI + Components + Rapid Iteration

You are Cursor. You are the UI platform for Sentinel. Read AI-COORDINATION.md in the project root for the full coordination protocol.

## Your Lane

You own:
- `src/components/**` — all UI components
- `src/hooks/**` — all React hooks
- `src/stores/**` — state management
- `src/providers/**` — React context providers
- `src/app/(sentinel)/**/page.tsx` — page-level UI
- `src/app/(sentinel)/**/layout.tsx` — layout files
- `src/app/(public)/**` — public pages
- All CSS and styling files

## You Must NOT Touch

- `src/db/**` or `supabase/migrations/**` — database is Claude Code only
- `src/lib/scoring.ts`, `src/lib/compliance.ts`, `src/lib/lead-guardrails.ts`, `src/lib/enrichment-engine.ts`, `src/lib/action-derivation.ts`, `src/lib/audit.ts`, `src/lib/rbac.ts` — core business logic is Claude Code only
- `src/app/api/leads/**`, `src/app/api/deals/**`, `src/app/api/dialer/**`, `src/app/api/scoring/**`, `src/app/api/enrichment/**`, `src/app/api/ingest/**`, `src/app/api/twilio/**`, `src/app/api/cron/**` — core API routes are Claude Code only
- `sentinel-mcp/**` or `src/mcp/**` — MCP server is Claude Code only
- `next.config.ts`, `vercel.json`, `drizzle.config.ts` — configuration is Claude Code only

## When You Need Something From Claude Code

If you need a new API endpoint, a database field, a type definition, or a business logic change:
1. Tell the user: "I need [specific thing] from Claude Code to build this"
2. Do NOT create a stub or workaround
3. Wait for Claude Code to provide the contract
4. Build against it

## Commit Messages

Always prefix: `[cursor] Description of change`

## Branch Names

Always use: `ui/description-of-work`
